summary:
16. Welcomes civil society contacts and encourages further engagement;

17. Underlines both sides' responsibility to ensure security and freedom of movement for UNOMIG, CIS peacekeeping force, and international personnel;

18. Welcomes efforts to implement zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse;

19. Extends UNOMIG's mandate until April 15, 2008;

20. Requests Secretary-General to support confidence-building measures and facilitate high-level meeting;

21. Supports Special Representative's efforts and Group of Friends' unified support;

22. Remains seized of the matter.
